headline: Air Fryer Breakfast Frittata
description: This versatile air fryer breakfast frittata recipe uses a cake pan that fits in the air fryer basket for fuss-free, light, and fluffy results.

video.description: Make this breakfast staple in your air fryer for a fun and easy twist on the classic frittata!
video.name: Air Fryer Breakfast Frittata

name: Air Fryer Breakfast Frittata
recipeIngredient: 0.25 pound breakfast sausage, fully cooked and crumbled
0.5 cup shredded Cheddar-Monterey Jack cheese blend

recipeInstructions.text: Preheat an air fryer to 360 degrees F (180 degrees C). Spray a nonstick 6x2-inch cake pan with cooking spray.
Combine sausage, eggs, cheese, bell pepper, green onion, and cayenne pepper in a large bowl; mix well to combine.
Pour egg mixture into the prepared cake pan.
Cook in the preheated air fryer until frittata is set, 18 to 20 minutes.

review.reviewBody: I used a reusable silicone air fryer liner. I didn't have the exact ingredients so I used 1/2 c. chopped mushrooms, 1 tsp. chopped green onions and 1/2 c. cheddar cheese and air fried for 17 minutes. The top was a bit dry but it was cooked through and delicious! I may still use the oven during cold weather but for warmer weather this is great so you don't heat up the kitchen! Thanks for sharing!

OK ............ I've made this 3 times before submitting my opinion / review. This is delicious as written, but I made some changes tonight I think are worthy of consideration. 1/2 pound of Jimmy Dean's HOT sausage 6 eggs Same amount and type of cheese. onion, and pepper 1 tsp. chopped jalapeno Preheat airfryer at 360 for 3 minutes then cook at 360 for 15, shut it off and let it sit for 5 minutes. Beautiful meal
Needs hot sauce or a little more seasoning.

This is a good, basic recipe. But depending on the size and shape of your air fryer you cannot preheat first and get your pan in without spilling egg mixture all over. I have a Cosori air fryer. It is square shaped. The round cake pan insert almost touches the sides. You really cannot lower a little pan into the basket without burning your hands. And doesn’t work well to wear mitts, because there’s just no space to get your hands in there. Turns out completely fine without pre-heating. ALSO This cook time is way off. At 360 the frittata will be completely done in about 6 minutes.

This came out very well on the first try! I changed up some of the ingredients (omitted onion; added mushrooms), and it came out great! I even made single-serving ones, and they were awesome too. I'm going to continue experimenting with different meats, veggies, seasonings, et al to see what else there is to enjoy with this basic dish.

Great recipe! So quick and easy! You could chop the vegetable the night before and through it together in the morning. I used Jimmy Dean pre-cooked sausage. But you could use ham, bacon or meatless sausage. The combinations of vegetable and meats are endless. It even looked pretty. Keeper!

LEFTOVER USE ALERT! Awesome recipe. I added leftover yuca fries. You can also use any left over fries like tater tots, or those fries you didn’t finish from dinner out last night! Chop them up and place at the bottom. Then follow this recipe.
So easy, perfect, and can easily be changed for what you have on hand. Thanks!

Main issue is that I just watched the video before making as pretty simple. The video says 180 degrees without specifying and I assumed Fahrenheit. Then afterwards I read the recipe and it says 180 degrees Celsius. Should have been noted on the video.

I used leftover vegetables. Normally I would sauté my vegetables and add about 2-3 table spoonfuls of Chinese cooking wine (Shao Xing wine) and a drizzle of sesame oil (you can find these at any Asian food store) when I'm cooking the vegetables. The wine and sesame oil will give it a fragrance but don't overdo the wine. If you use leftovers, you can stir-fry it again in a tablespoon of olive oil on a pan, add a bit of mushrooms or fresh vegetables to give it a fresher taste. I just added the egg mixture in the baking tin and topped it off with a combination of mozzarella and cheddar pizza topping cheese and baked it for 18 minutes in the airfryer. Et voila! Delicious.

The Air Fryer Breakfast Frittata was delicious! But I had to make a modification. I did not have a metal pan so I used a glass mixing bowl that fit in the air fryer. I found I had to stir it two times because it was not cooking on the bottom. I don't know if that is because of the shape of the bowl. I also added mushrooms and used turkey sausage instead of regular sausage. Turkey sausage tasted great as a substitute.
